**Feature: Squire of Solamnia**：You gain the Squire of Solamnia feat.
In addition, the Knights of Solamnia provide you free, modest lodging and food at any of their fortresses or encampments.
**Building a Knight of Solamnia Character**：Any class that has martial prowess can be a good fit in the Knights of Solamnia. Fighter and paladin make up the bulk of the knighthood's forces. Cleric (often with the Cleric domain) can also be found among the knights' ranks.
For a more unusual take on a Knight of Solamnia character, consider playing a bard of the Bard (or the Bard from Xanathar's Guide to Everything) or a barbarian devoted to the ideals of the nature god Habbakuk (perhaps adopting the barbarian from Xanathar's Guide to Everything).
**Knight of Solamnia Trinkets**：When you make your character, roll once on the Knight of Solamnia Trinkets table instead of on the Trinket in the Player's Handbook for your starting trinket.
